# Git Commit & Push Preferences

## Commit Messages
- Use conventional commits format: `type(scope): description`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
- Example: `feat(two_wheeler): add RL training environment`
- Use imperative mood ("add" not "added")

## Files to Include
- Include: source/isaaclab_tasks/**/* (IsaacLab), two_wheeler/**/* (Master)
- Exclude by default: *.cmd, build artifacts (e.g. 2.7.0+cu128), __pycache__, .pyc

## Push Behavior
- Push to origin after each commit: no (ask first)

## Default Branch
- main
